out Julia (doesn't love Roy), Rory (unloved husband, brother of Frank) and Frank (son of a gun, daredevil, lost his life to the Cenobites) is a bit too common and predictable. Kristy (a neighbor) sees that Julia brings men into the house she leads to the upper room. What's the reason for doing this? What about Rory in the end? The characters and their behavior are the weak element here. First you don't like them too much and then you don't understand their action. The eeriest and uncanniest elements are the Cenobites. They are absolute cult. The rest is insignificant in my opinion. There are better works out from Clive Barker, e.g. The Books of Blood or Coldhearted Canyon (one of my alltime favorites). Recommended only because it's a classic and because of the Cenobites!","rating":3,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/10477405?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"horror","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/10477405?shelf=horror"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3372683366"},"likeCount":106,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":9,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v3.RXhFujhdrub5lCno":{"id":"kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v3.RXhFujhdrub5lCno","__typename":"Contributor","works":{"__typename":"ContributorWorksConnection","totalCount":13}},"User:28225370":{"id":28225370,"__typename":"User","legacyId":28225370,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1607526135i/28225370._UX200_CR0,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":true,"textReviewsCount":814,"viewableName":"Sadie Hartmann","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/28225370-sadie-hartmann","contributor":{"__ref":"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v3.RXhFujhdrub5lCno"},"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":